# Auto-detect text files and normalize line endings
* text=auto eol=lf

# Force LF on Godot text resources to keep diffs clean across OSes
*.gd text eol=lf
*.tres text eol=lf
*.tscn text eol=lf
*.godot text eol=lf
*.cfg text eol=lf

# We previously routed every binary through Git LFS. The free LFS
# bandwidth budget (1 GB/month on github.com) drained quickly because
# every CI run pulls every job's LFS objects, and a single 30 MB music
# WAV multiplied that out. We now keep small/static art and fonts in
# plain git and reserve LFS for genuinely large binaries (AdMob AAR
# files in Phase 6, large compressed audio in OGG, etc.).
*.so filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.dll filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# Audio: kept in plain git too, since OGG/MP3 of a single 2-5 minute track
# is small enough (a few MB) that LFS overhead — and especially the per-CI
# bandwidth cost — outweighs the benefit. Revisit when a track tops 20 MB.

# *.png, *.jpg, *.jpeg, *.gif, *.webp, *.wav, *.ttf, *.otf are kept in
# plain git: spritesheets are small (kilobytes), GUT's vendored TTFs
# don't change, and tap-style SFX are well under 2 MB each.
